  <id>com.example.secrets</id> <!-- Replace with your actual App ID -->

  <name>Secrets</name>
  <summary>A clean interface for managing a pass repository</summary>

  <metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
  <project_license>MIT</project_license> <!-- Replace with your actual license if not MIT -->

  <description>
    <p>
      Secrets provides a user-friendly graphical interface for managing passwords
      stored with 'pass', the standard unix password manager.
    </p>
    <p>Key Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Browse your password store in a tree view.</li>
      <li>Copy passwords to the clipboard (cleared automatically after a timeout).</li>
      <li>Add new passwords and edit existing ones through a dialog.</li>
      <li>Generate strong, random passwords.</li>
      <li>Synchronize changes with a remote git repository (git pull/push).</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

